{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":244,"record_hash":"sha256:5e0af263424487c4f49642f4eb66e84a470841e4ee4971e5d7342fc50569b97b","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:21:11.526Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Not huge in code. Medium in coordination.\n\nI checked GitMeta’s internals: `apply_edits` already wraps edits in a SQLite savepoint, and scalar `set_value` already exists. Savepoints are nestable there, so adding scalar `SetValue` to `MetaEdit` is mostly plumbing, not a redesign.\n\nLikely change:\n\n```rust\npub enum MetaEdit<'a> {\n    ListAppend { key: &'a str, entries: &'a [ListEntry] },\n    SetAdd { key: &'a str, members: &'a [String] },\n    SetValue { key: &'a str, value: &'a MetaValue },\n}\n```\n\nThen `Store::apply_edits` handles:\n\n```rust\nMetaEdit::SetValue { key, value } => {\n    self.set_value(target, key, value, email, timestamp)?;\n}\n```\n\nWhat needs touching:\n\n- `git-meta-lib/src/types.rs`: add variant + constructor\n- `git-meta-lib/src/db/lists.rs`: update validation/match in `apply_edits`\n- `[REDACTED:entropy].rs`: docs maybe\n- tests: add “set + list append + set add rolls back together”\n- maybe rename docs from “list/set edits” to “metadata edits”\n\nThe annoying bit: GitMeta is an external pinned git dependency here, not just another crate in this repo. So the work is small, but we’d need to patch upstream GitMeta or point GitButler at a new rev. That’s the coordination cost.\n\nMy take: it’s worth doing if we expect turns to be real. If we want a throwaway spike, use list/set-only storage. But for the actual implementation, extending GitMeta is the cleaner move.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:21:11.526Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}